- ( clippers buzzing )
- ( chatter)

02:35.450 --> 02:37.918
- Morning, y'all!
- Men: Morning.

02:37.950 --> 02:40.282
How is everybody?

02:40.320 --> 02:42.527
Looking like a queen
as always, Nova.

02:44.260 --> 02:46.194
Got some heads up in here
this morning, D.

02:46.230 --> 02:47.891
No doubt.
Business been good.

02:47.930 --> 02:49.227
( chuckles )

02:49.270 --> 02:50.897
Thank you.

02:50.930 --> 02:53.433
- ( scoffs )
- ( change rattles )

02:53.470 --> 02:57.236
This can's
a little light, y'all.

02:57.270 --> 02:58.567
Psst, psst.

03:01.840 --> 03:03.546
Take this to the lady.

03:05.280 --> 03:07.419
Thank you, honey.
You're a sweetie.

03:08.780 --> 03:11.283
If you come back through
a little later,

03:11.320 --> 03:14.312
I promise you
it'll be straight.

03:14.360 --> 03:17.227
Tips today-- I want 'em
in this here can, fellas.

03:17.260 --> 03:18.750
Y'all feel me?

03:18.790 --> 03:21.725
Every one of y'all
know somebody sitting
up in the OPP now

03:21.760 --> 03:23.625
or did _some time there
In the past

03:23.670 --> 03:26.662
'cause they couldn't raise
300, $400 to post bail.

03:26.700 --> 03:28.839
A community bail fund
could change that.

03:31.440 --> 03:33.305
I'm not here
to call anybody out.

03:33.340 --> 03:36.446
I appreciate y'all
giving what you can,

03:36.480 --> 03:38.471
but do this for me.

03:38.510 --> 03:41.445
Come out to the community
fundraiser tonight

03:41.480 --> 03:44.278
and show your love
with your presence, too?

03:44.320 --> 03:46.311
- Yeah?
- Man: Yes, ma'am.

03:46.360 --> 03:48.351
And you, too?

03:48.390 --> 03:50.278
I'll see y'all later.

03:50.330 --> 03:51.820
- ( door opens )
- Man: All right, girl.

03:51.860 --> 03:52.895
Man #2:
Take care, now.

03:54.460 --> 03:56.792
( news radio playing
in background )

03:56.830 --> 03:58.866
- Hey.
- Violet: Hey!

03:58.900 --> 04:02.609
Dang! You got it
going on in here,
Aunt Vi!

04:02.640 --> 04:05.609
Yeah, and the last batch
will be out in a few minutes.

04:05.640 --> 04:07.608
( grunts )

04:07.640 --> 04:09.801
( sniffs )
I don't know how I'm gonna
repay you for all the time

04:09.850 --> 04:12.842
- and energy you're
putting into this.
- Repay me?

04:12.880 --> 04:14.768
I'm grateful, Aunt Vi.

04:14.820 --> 04:18.449
And I know
our volunteers will be, too,
once they get a taste.

04:19.960 --> 04:21.552
- Charley here?
- Yeah.

04:21.590 --> 04:24.479
She fixing to take Micah
to summer school.

04:24.530 --> 04:26.498
He went back already?

04:26.530 --> 04:28.998
Back?
He's been for three days.

04:29.030 --> 04:30.429
How's he doing?

04:30.470 --> 04:33.769
Well, he ain't eating
much of anything

04:33.800 --> 04:37.463
and acting like
nothing's happened,
so I don't know.

04:40.810 --> 04:42.004
Nephew!

04:47.080 --> 04:50.049
( knocking )

04:55.420 --> 04:57.752
Hey, nephew.

04:57.790 --> 04:58.722
Hey.

05:09.970 --> 05:11.528
How's school?

05:11.570 --> 05:12.901
It's all right.

05:19.550 --> 05:22.940
Anything you wanna...

05:22.990 --> 05:24.639
talk about?

05:26.120 --> 05:28.008
No. Ijust...

05:29.760 --> 05:30.988
I'm fine.

05:33.730 --> 05:35.925
I don't know what
those police said to you...

05:39.940 --> 05:41.532
or what they did...

05:43.710 --> 05:45.837
but we can talk
about it.

05:47.840 --> 05:49.740
We can talk
about anything.

05:55.480 --> 05:58.881
I'm fine...
Aunt Nova, really.

06:18.470 --> 06:19.630
Mill loan come through?

06:19.680 --> 06:22.137
Yeah, should close
the next day or so.

06:22.180 --> 06:23.647
At least it better.

06:23.680 --> 06:25.648
You've got this,
Charley.

06:25.680 --> 06:26.942
Harvest is right around
the corner,

06:26.980 --> 06:28.868
and I've gotta get
these renovations going.

06:28.920 --> 06:31.912
So it's back to NoLa
for another dog and pony show?

06:35.760 --> 06:37.751
I'm meeting with Davis
this morning.

06:37.790 --> 06:39.929
Divorce_mediation.
It's our final sessnon.

06:39.960 --> 06:42.827
- Why didn't you say something?
- Violet: Say something
about what?

06:44.970 --> 06:47.438
What?

06:47.470 --> 06:49.836
My final divorce mediation
with Davis

06:49.870 --> 06:51.565
is scheduled
for this morning.

06:51.610 --> 06:52.736
- Oh, Charley, baby--
- I'm coming with you.

06:52.780 --> 06:54.429
No, no one
is coming with me.

06:54.480 --> 06:56.038
This is why
I didn't say anything.

06:56.080 --> 06:58.901
- I know how y'all are.
- That's right! We're family.

06:58.950 --> 07:02.943
Look, I am perfectly capable
of dealing with this by myself.

07:02.990 --> 07:04.480
And what about Micah?

07:04.520 --> 07:05.782
How's he dealing
with this?

07:05.820 --> 07:09.119
I know it's hard,
but he's resilient.

07:09.160 --> 07:10.718
It's a process.

07:10.760 --> 07:13.649
Well, that boy has a lot
to process right about now

07:13.700 --> 07:15.850
between this
and being stopped
by the police.

07:15.900 --> 07:18.869
I'm here for him.
He knows that.

07:18.900 --> 07:21.539
Hi. You ready?

07:21.570 --> 07:23.800
Violet: Hey, baby.
Let me fix you some breakfast.

07:23.840 --> 07:26.707
- No, thank you.
- Micah, you need
to eat something.

07:26.740 --> 07:28.071
We'll stop on the way.

07:34.550 --> 07:35.744
Bye.

07:41.590 --> 07:43.979
Man:
Well, smce you're
going in late,

07:44.030 --> 07:47.898
I'm thinking hybrid soybean
be your best bet, MG V.

07:47.930 --> 07:50.160
Now, it's gonna cost you
a little more up front,

07:50.200 --> 07:51.792
but it grows
to canopy faster

07:51.830 --> 07:54.697
so you'll save
on weed control later.

07:54.740 --> 07:56.958
( chicks chirping )

07:57.010 --> 07:58.568
How much more?

07:58.610 --> 08:00.737
( music playing
on stereo )

08:05.910 --> 08:07.639
Blue. Hey!

08:07.680 --> 08:09.648
You can't just go
in people's stuff
like that.

08:09.690 --> 08:11.112
I'm feeding
the chicks.

08:11.150 --> 08:13.584
I think
they're hungry.

08:13.620 --> 08:15.588
You know the drill,
don't you, Blue?

08:15.620 --> 08:17.588
Ernest used
to bring him here.

08:17.630 --> 08:18.983
Come on, Pop,
I'll show you.

08:19.030 --> 08:20.691
Just go ahead
while I work you up
a price.

08:20.730 --> 08:22.197
- All right.
- ( chuckles )

08:26.200 --> 08:27.758
( chirping )

08:27.800 --> 08:30.007
- You can pet it.
- I could pet it?

08:30.040 --> 08:31.769
It's really soft.

08:33.780 --> 08:35.668
What's up, buddy?

08:35.710 --> 08:37.143
( chuckles )

08:40.180 --> 08:42.614
You know, your working
the farm with your sisters,

08:42.650 --> 08:44.880
this soybean planting,

08:44.920 --> 08:48.287
you're thinking
like a real farmer.

08:48.320 --> 08:51.027
I appreciate that,
Mr. Cyrus.

08:51.060 --> 08:52.698
Ernest is smiling.

08:52.730 --> 08:54.721
( chuckles )

08:57.230 --> 08:59.266
( scoffs )

08:59.300 --> 09:00.699
3,200?

09:00.740 --> 09:02.298
Come on, Blue.

09:02.340 --> 09:06.709
- ( piano music playing )
_ ( keyboard clicking,
printer whirs )

09:06.740 --> 09:10.141
- The seeds are
for Blue's Corner?
- That's right, Blue's Corner.

09:12.850 --> 09:14.317
I'm sorry,
but your account is--

09:14.350 --> 09:16.614
- What? Not enough money?
- Oh, no, it's not that.

09:16.650 --> 09:18.845
The signatory requirements
have changed.

09:18.890 --> 09:22.053
It now requires another
signature for withdrawals--

09:22.090 --> 09:24.024
Charley Bordelon-West.

09:27.130 --> 09:29.894
Can you let this slide now,
and I'll talk to her?

09:31.630 --> 09:33.939
I can't.
Bank policy.

09:33.970 --> 09:37.133
Bank policy.

09:37.170 --> 09:38.660
Come on,
let's go, buddy.

09:38.710 --> 09:41.838
Oh, uh,
can he have this?

09:41.880 --> 09:43.905
- Yeah.
- Thank you.

09:43.950 --> 09:46.839
- You want one, Pop?
- I'm good, Blue.
Come on.

09:50.890 --> 09:52.016
( music playing )

09:52.050 --> 09:53.915
- Roberta.
- Yes, ma'am?

09:53.960 --> 09:55.882
Excuse me, miss.
Come on.

09:55.920 --> 09:57.820
What's going on,
fellas?

09:57.860 --> 09:59.691
We're a little backed up,
but I'm gonna take care of you.

09:59.730 --> 10:01.357
Okay?
All right.

10:01.400 --> 10:04.164
- Aunt Vi!
- Wai-- hey.

10:04.200 --> 10:06.839
I'm glad to see you.
What you been doing?

10:06.870 --> 10:08.792
- Helping Pop.
- Well, that's good.

10:08.840 --> 10:11.229
- He needs help, huh?
- Back taking orders?

10:11.270 --> 10:14.034
- I thought you was managing.
- Don't mess with me.

10:14.080 --> 10:17.106
I am down two waitresses,
I got a leak in the kitchen,

10:17.150 --> 10:18.276
and the freezer broke.

10:18.310 --> 10:20.119
Can't serve any bacon
or sausage

10:20.150 --> 10:21.811
on account
of the health department.

10:21.850 --> 10:24.011
These folks was ready to fight
up in here this morning.

10:24.050 --> 10:26.985
- Damn, that's rough.
- So, if y'all want
something to eat,

10:27.020 --> 10:28.351
you're gonna have
to be patient.

10:28.390 --> 10:32.258
Matter of fact,
I was hoping for
a favor, Aunt Vi.

10:32.290 --> 10:33.723
Well, what's that?

10:33.760 --> 10:37.025
I was wondering
if you could watch
Blue for me.

10:37.070 --> 10:39.732
- Where's Darla?
- She working.

10:39.770 --> 10:43.069
I got some business I need
to handle on the farm.

10:43.110 --> 10:48.070
Well, you know
Blue_ is welcome
here With me anytime.

10:48.110 --> 10:50.442
- Thanks, Aunt Vi.
- Mm-hmm.

10:50.480 --> 10:52.914
Can we have spaghetti
for dinner?

10:52.950 --> 10:54.815
Dinner, baby?
What are you talking about?

10:54.850 --> 10:56.818
Pop is taking Mama
on a date.

10:56.850 --> 10:59.887
- Ralph Angel: Ain't nobody
ask you all that--
- ( smooching )

10:59.920 --> 11:02.309
All right, baby.
Listen, I'm working.

11:02.360 --> 11:04.749
Go behind the counter
and get the sugar packets

11:04.790 --> 11:06.280
and restock the tables.

11:06.330 --> 11:08.059
- Okay.
- Go.

11:10.730 --> 11:13.130
I wanna do something
special for Darla.

11:15.300 --> 11:17.029
So?

11:17.070 --> 11:19.334
Well, yeah,
you know I'm not gonna
turn down a chance

11:19.370 --> 11:21.429
to spend time
with that boy.

11:21.480 --> 11:23.072
Thank you.

11:23.110 --> 11:25.078
You sure you know
what you're doing?

11:25.110 --> 11:28.079
Ahem, look, you talk
to Charley today?

11:28.120 --> 11:30.418
Not since this morning.
Why?

11:30.450 --> 11:32.008
I need to talk to her,
that's all.

11:32.050 --> 11:35.713
Well, today is
Charley's divorce mediation.

11:35.760 --> 11:37.785
I didn't know.

11:37.830 --> 11:41.152
I don't know what's going on
between the two of you
at the moment,

11:41.200 --> 11:45.159
but I need you to give her
some grace today.

11:55.080 --> 11:57.002
- Remy: Farm account?
- Roberta: Y'all good?

11:57.050 --> 11:58.802
Yeah, baby, thanks.

11:58.850 --> 12:00.772
Why would she have said
anything to me about it?

12:00.820 --> 12:02.947
Y'all been working
on the mill loan together.

12:02.990 --> 12:04.844
You was organizing
the farmers for it.

12:04.890 --> 12:06.448
- I figured you probably--
- You figured wrong.

12:08.090 --> 12:10.058
I didn't mean
no disrespect.

12:11.360 --> 12:13.794
Oh...

12:13.830 --> 12:15.252
your sister and me...

12:17.000 --> 12:19.161
Look, it's just
about that mill.

12:19.200 --> 12:22.192
It's about the mill
and getting through
the harvest, and that's all.

12:22.240 --> 12:24.208
And if there's something
on that farm that needs fixing,

12:24.240 --> 12:26.367
I'm sure Charley
will spend money on it.

12:28.140 --> 12:30.199
I'm planting
a soybean crop.

12:34.480 --> 12:36.118
Got it.

12:36.150 --> 12:38.015
And you need
to buy seed?

12:42.830 --> 12:46.084
I'm tired of going to Charley
every time I need something.

12:47.230 --> 12:49.551
This is about
the future, right, man?

12:49.600 --> 12:52.125
Pops wanted me
to keep farming.

12:52.170 --> 12:55.162
He held on long as he did
so we could build a business,

12:55.200 --> 12:57.202
and that's what I wanna do.

13:02.910 --> 13:04.172
Look here.

13:04.210 --> 13:07.179
I can see you wanna make
your own moves, all right?

13:07.220 --> 13:08.573
Why don't you try
to get a microloan

13:08.620 --> 13:10.087
from the Farm Services
Agency?

13:10.120 --> 13:12.338
Ain't nobody gonna
give me money, Remy.

13:12.390 --> 13:14.858
Not on parole.
Shit, no credit, too?

13:14.890 --> 13:17.552
- Come on.
- Don't be so quick to say
what somebody gonna do.

13:17.590 --> 13:19.228
_ Look at--
listen to me, man.

13:19.260 --> 13:22.423
I believe in you,
and I believe in that farm.

13:22.460 --> 13:25.497
And whatever's happening
or not happening between me
and your sister,

13:25.530 --> 13:27.896
that's not gonna change
the love I got for your daddy,

13:27.940 --> 13:31.307
for your family,
and that land,
you hear me?

13:31.340 --> 13:35.174
That microloan program
is for young farmers
like yourself

13:35.210 --> 13:38.577
with no capital, little credit,
but who are actually farming

13:38.610 --> 13:41.443
and have small needs
here and there.

13:41.480 --> 13:44.085
So long as you got a job,
a farm to work,

13:44.120 --> 13:45.587
and you never been
convicted of growing

13:45.620 --> 13:49.386
or distributing drugs--
which you haven't been, right?

13:49.420 --> 13:51.888
( laughs )
Right?

13:51.930 --> 13:53.352
That means
you're eligible.

13:54.630 --> 13:58.293
S-so maybe
I could, like...

13:58.330 --> 14:00.059
do it by myself?

14:00.100 --> 14:03.501
Yeah, maybe you could
do it by yourself.

14:12.980 --> 14:14.470
Ralph Angel:
I'll see y'all.

14:14.520 --> 14:16.442
- Hey.
- What's going on?

14:16.480 --> 14:19.916
- Aunt Vi here?
- Yeah, she with Blue.
They in the back office.

14:21.360 --> 14:23.920
I got stuff to do, Nova.
Farm don't just run itself.

14:23.960 --> 14:25.655
I know it don't!

14:25.690 --> 14:28.295
I know
you working hard, bro.

14:28.330 --> 14:30.195
Like I said,
they in the back there.

14:30.230 --> 14:32.095
Listen, I got a bunch of food
and stuff that I'm hauling

14:32.130 --> 14:33.631
to this fundraiser tonight.

14:33.670 --> 14:36.662
- I was wondering-- maybe--
- I can't. I got errands.

14:36.700 --> 14:39.999
- Maybe I could use your truck.
- Plus my truck's already
loaded up.

14:40.040 --> 14:41.928
You oughta come
and check it out.

14:41.980 --> 14:44.073
Raising money
for a bail fund.

14:45.410 --> 14:48.049
Could always use more brothers
supporting the cause.

14:50.150 --> 14:54.189
Nova, I ain't got time
for this right now. Bye.

14:59.090 --> 15:00.955
Excuse me, brother,
how you doing?

15:01.000 --> 15:02.399
You wanna _come_out
to the community bail fund?

15:02.430 --> 15:03.692
Yeah, all right.

15:03.730 --> 15:05.493
You, too.
Wanna come?
Check it out.

15:05.530 --> 15:08.363
We'll just take
a few deep breaths
before we go in.

15:08.400 --> 15:10.038
We should have you out
in plenty of time

15:10.070 --> 15:11.503
for you to do
what you need to do.

15:11.540 --> 15:15.408
And remember, they have
agreed in principle
to everything.

15:15.440 --> 15:17.408
You're in great shape.

15:17.450 --> 15:19.509
( sighs )
I just want this
to be over.

15:19.550 --> 15:23.088
Eyes on the prize, Charley.
You're almost there.

15:30.690 --> 15:33.454
Woman:
Charley, Davis,

15:33.500 --> 15:37.061
this is the last
of our scheduled
mediation seSSIons.

15:37.100 --> 15:38.465
I know it hasn't always
been easy,

15:38.500 --> 15:40.536
but I want to commend you both
on your willingness

15:40.570 --> 15:44.062
to seek out common ground
during this process.

